For runing test need:

1.Configure file cometd/service/src/test/java/conf/test-configuration.xml

  <configuration clients="15" repeat="1" sleep-connection="500" sleep-sending="200">
    <container containerStart="false" port="8080" home=""/>
    <messages>
      <message broadcast="false" id="1">hello</message>
      <message broadcast="true" id="2">hello!!!</message>
    </messages>
    <cometd-url>http://localhost:8080/cometd/cometd</cometd-url>
    <base-url>http://localhost:8080/rest/</base-url>
    <channels>
        <channel>/eXo/comedt/test</channel>
    </channels>
  </configuration>
  
  This test running two servers tomcat (in role eXo-server) and jetty (cometd server).
  In this configure say that we do 15 cometd connection with interval 500 ms. sending 2
  messages (1 broadcast) with time-out 200 ms, 'base-url' - URL of eXo-server,
  clients subscribe to '/eXo/comedt/test' channel.
  During testing run 2 test:
    - TransportCometdTest - the test with Cometd server that work on Jetty, and eXo server on Tomcat.
    - LocalCometdTest - the test then Comet server and eXo server work on Tomcat (it not work with many connections, so must be exclude) 
      "comedt-url" use with local test.
2.Also need configure cometd/service/src/main/java/conf/configuration.xml        
  detail information about how to config server please visit 
  http://wiki.exoplatform.org/xwiki/bin/view/Internal+Space/Cometd+Cluster+with+LoadBalancing
3.Need build projects with cometd/pom.xml.

4.Go to cometd/service and run 
  mvn clean install -f pom-test.xml -Dexo.test.skip=false -Djetty.home="./target/jetty" 
  You must see information about count connected clients and messges that they get.